body_html:
@yangjunpro issues should be created for bugs or feature requests.

Bugs should be accompanied by instructions on how to reproduce and feature requests should identify the desired functionality to be developed.

As far as I can tell, this issue is neither a bug nor a feature request. You are welcome to reopen this issue if you encounter a (performance) bug and can share steps on how to reproduce it. If instead you prefer to address what you believe is the limitation yourself, you can create a PR with your contribution when it is ready.
